  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1274",
  "title": "Automatically deploy branches (= +PRS) to gh-pages for preview",
  "body": "One thing we miss right now on the collaboration part is to be able to quickly visually see the result of a PR.\n\nThis could be solved by:\n- deploy every opened PR to http://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/pr/#number/..\n- it will make the PR docs accessible and possibly any change/new example. Much easier to comment/iterate\n- we can use travis hooks on PRS, and reuse the gh-pages script (with some little tweaking so that we do not erase anything) to deploy\n- after publishing, we should post a comment in the github issue\n- then about cleaning merged PRS. When the v2 branch is built, we just list all closed PRS and we delete possible artifacts (or we use a github hook to do so, but never did that) from gh-pages\n\nWhat do you think?\n",
